{"lemma":"دَكُّ","slug":"دَكُّ","root":"د.ك.ك","root_slug":"د-ك-ك","root_link":"/words/roots/د-ك-ك","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"دَكّ","root":"دكك","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12843","n12849","n12850"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%8F%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"alternative form of دَقَّ (daqqa, “to crush, to pound, to beat, to press down”)","tags":["alt-of","alternative"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fill by pressing into, to fill up with earth or the like, for example to charge (i.e. to fill the charge into) a firearm (which was done with the مِدَكّ (midakk, “ramrod”))"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of دَكَّ (dakka) (form I), alternative form of دَقّ (daqq)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"level and depressed ground, even earth"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"elevating mass of earth, mound"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"common plural of أَدَكّ (ʔadakk, “of a pressed-down back”)","tags":["common","form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew דיכא (to crush)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12843","headword_ar":"دَكَّ","root":"dk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dak~N","text_ar":"دَكٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He broke,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crushed, in any manner;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bruised, brayed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pounded;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beat with a thing so as to break"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crush; i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daq~a","text_ar":"دَقَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He threw down, pulled to pieces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"demolished."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He broke"},{"kind":"text","text":"a wall, and a mountain. (Lth, TA.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He beat"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and broke"},{"kind":"text","text":"it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to lay"},{"kind":"text","text":"it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"even with the ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) Hence the saying in the Kur [lxix. 14],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faduk~ataA dak~apF waAHidapF","text_ar":"فَدُكَّتَا دَكَّةً وَاحِدَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And they shall be beaten together with one beating, and the whole shall become fine dust:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they shall both be spread with one spreading, so as to become an even ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd.) [For]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dak~a AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"دَكَّ الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n. as above, (K, TA,) means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made even the elevations and depressions of the earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*aA","text_ar":"اَذَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duk~ati AlA^aroDu dak~FA","text_ar":"دُكَّتِ الاَرْضُ دَكًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [lxxxix. 22], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When the earth shall be made level, without hills,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Arafeh, Bd,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and without mountains:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or it means,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall become fine dust scattered:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall be shaken so that every building thereon shall be demolished and non-existent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dak~N","text_ar":"دَكٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dak~N","text_ar":"دَكٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spreading"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabos","text_ar":"كَبْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kanos","text_ar":"كَنْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put in the CK]) of earth,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and making"},{"kind":"text","text":"it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"even."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) When a roof, or flat house-top, has been spread with earth ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kubiasa biAlt~uraAbi","text_ar":"كُبَِسَ بِالتُّرَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duk~a Alt~uraAbu Ealayohi","text_ar":"دُكَّ التُّرَابُ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Earth was spread upon it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dak~a Alt~uraAba EalaY Almay~iti","text_ar":"دَكَّ التُّرَابَ عَلَى المَيِّتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dak~N","text_ar":"دَكٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He poured earth upon the corpse."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, AHn.) ―         -b3-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"filling up"},{"kind":"text","text":"a well (K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with earth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dakodakapN","text_ar":"دَكْدَكَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dakakotu Alr~akiY~a","text_ar":"دَكَكْتُ الرَّكِىَّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I filled up the wells with earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~akiY~a","text_ar":"الرَّكِىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dakodaka","text_ar":"دَكْدَكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He filled up the wells with earth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dak~ahu","text_ar":"دَكَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pushed him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thrust him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sak~ahu","text_ar":"صَكَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lak~ahu","text_ar":"لَكَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (As, TA.) ―         -b5-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dak~a jaAriyatahu","text_ar":"دَكَّ جَارِيَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distressed his young woman,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female slave, by throwing his weight upon her when"},{"kind":"page_break","n":899},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desiring to compress her."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rak~a","text_ar":"رَكَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dak~a Ald~aAb~apa biAls~ayori","text_ar":"دَكَّ الدَّابَّةَ بِالسَّيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He distressed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jaded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fatigued, the beast by journeying."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duk~a Alr~ajulu","text_ar":"دُكَّ الرَّجُلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dak~atohu AlHum~aY","text_ar":"دَكَّتْهُ الحُمَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dak~ahu AlmaraDu","text_ar":"دَكَّهُ المَرَضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fever,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disease, weakened the man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became sick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ill."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dak~N","text_ar":"دَكٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sending forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"camels"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all together."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn- 'Abbád, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","Bd","AZ"]},{"entry_id":"n12849","headword_ar":"دَكٌّ","root":"dk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"An"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"even,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"level,"},{"kind":"text","text":"place; (K;) [and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adak~u","text_ar":"اَدَكُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is shown by an explanation of its fem. in this paragraph:] or land, or ground,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broken, and made even:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN dak~N","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ دَكٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Akh, S:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dukuwkN","text_ar":"دُكُوكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) Hence, in the Kur [vii. 139 and xviii. 98],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEalahu dak~FA","text_ar":"جَعَلَهُ دَكًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Akh, S, TA,) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the former instance, and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall make it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the latter instance,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"even,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"level,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, Az, Ibn-'Arafeh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without any hill:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn- 'Arafeh: [this addition relating to the former instance:]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crumbled:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh, * Bd:) or, accord. to Akh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dak~FA","text_ar":"دَكًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be here an inf. n.; as though the meaning were ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dak~ahu dak~FA","text_ar":"دَكَّهُ دَكًّا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": [see 1:] or it may be elliptical, meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEalahu *aA dak~K","text_ar":"جَعَلَهُ ذَا دَكٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": another reading is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEalahu dak~aA='a","text_ar":"جَعَلَهُ دَكَّا=ءَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) meaning in the former instance"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hill rising from the ground like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dak~apa","text_ar":"دَكَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ksh:) or meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEalahu A^aroDFA dak~aA='a","text_ar":"جَعَلَهُ اَرْضًا دَكَّا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it even,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"level, ground;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh, Bd;) because the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jabal","text_ar":"جَبَل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[to which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dk~A='","text_ar":"دكّا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"virtually relates] is masc. (S.) ―         -b2-  Also, [as a subst.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Even,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"level, sand;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dak~apN","text_ar":"دَكَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl. [of either, agreeably with analogy,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dikaAkN","text_ar":"دِكَاكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hill, of dust"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth, such as is called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tal~","text_ar":"تَلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tal~","text_ar":"تَلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) in some of the copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Altk~","text_ar":"التكّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~l","text_ar":"التّل"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Akh","TA","Ksh","K","L"]},{"entry_id":"n12850","headword_ar":"دُكٌّ","root":"dk","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A low mountain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an elevated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overlooking, hill of mould,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clay, in which is somewhat of ruggedness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dikakapN","text_ar":"دِكَكَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (As, S, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dikakN","text_ar":"دِكَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. another, though irregular, pl. of the same,] is said to signify"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiyraAn","text_ar":"قِيرَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small isolated mountains,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knolls of mountains,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaArapN","text_ar":"قَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"breaking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crumbling, down:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disintegrated"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hills,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mountains, such as are called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiDaAb","text_ar":"هِضَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adak~u","text_ar":"اَدَكُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which it is a pl.]       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strong and bulky."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","As","TA"]}]}}